Architectural Overview:

     Processing.cpp is functionalities that we implemented in our gerp class 
     and is used to index all of the file contents and hashTables. For example
     nonStripAlpha is used as a response to the query input and additionally,
     how we store a given word and its location.

     Sentence.h is the "key" for our hash Table on how to access our Vector of 
     Files. Given a word, we find the index in our hash Table and access the 
     file number and line number. We have the first index of each vector of 
     Lines be the path of the line itself, so we can print our the path to a 
     certain line and its content with its file number and line number as 
     coordinates. And since vectors are indexed at 0, having it so that the 
     path is the first index of every vector of Lines makes accessing a 
     particular line straight forward. 
     
     If we want to access the first file first line, then 1 1 does this sequence

     Basic Level Structure of our implementation:


     hashVector : 

       Bucket 1   Bucket 2   Bucket 3   Bucket 4   Bucket 5 
     |  pair  1 |  pair  2 |  pair  3 |  pair  4 |  pair  5 |

     In each pair, there contains a sentence Struct:
     
     Sentence Struct:

     fileNum  -> what File Number the user wants to access
     lineNum  -> what Line Number the user wants to access
     word     -> the word the query wants to find


         File 1      File 2      File 3      File 4     <- Vector of Files

     |   Path 1  |   Path 2  |   Path 3  |   Path 4  |  <- Each Line is a 
     |   Line 1  |   Line 2  |   Line 3  |   Line 4  |     pair of T/F and 
     |           |           |           |           |     the line content


     Return: Path 1

